### File Structure
```
GymMembership/
│
├── app.py
├── templates/
│   ├── dashboard.html
│   ├── membership_plans.html
│   ├── plan_details.html
│   ├── class_schedule.html
│   ├── trainer_profiles.html
│   ├── trainer_detail.html
│   ├── pt_booking.html
│   ├── workout_records.html
│   └── log_workout.html
│
├── static/
│   ├── css/
│   │   └── styles.css
│   ├── js/
│   │   └── scripts.js
│   └── images/
│       └── (trainer photos, icons, etc.)
│
└── data/
    ├── memberships.txt
    ├── classes.txt
    ├── trainers.txt
    ├── bookings.txt
    └── workouts.txt
```

### File Descriptions
- **app.py**  
  The main backend Python application file. It handles routing, data reading/writing from/to local text files in the `data/` directory, and serves the HTML templates. Since the application is not very complex, all backend logic (including data management, filtering, and page rendering) will be contained here.

- **templates/**  
  Directory containing all HTML template files for the web pages, each corresponding to one of the nine pages specified in the requirements. These templates will use Python templating (e.g., Jinja2 if using Flask) to dynamically render data.

  - `dashboard.html` — Dashboard page with navigation and member highlights.  
  - `membership_plans.html` — Displays membership plans with filtering and navigation.  
  - `plan_details.html` — Shows detailed information about a selected membership plan.  
  - `class_schedule.html` — Displays class schedules with search and filter options.  
  - `trainer_profiles.html` — Lists trainers with search and filter capabilities.  
  - `trainer_detail.html` — Detailed trainer profile page with booking option.  
  - `pt_booking.html` — Personal training booking page with form inputs.  
  - `workout_records.html` — Displays workout history and filtering options.  
  - `log_workout.html` — Form page to log new workout records.

- **static/**  
  Contains static assets such as CSS stylesheets, JavaScript files for client-side interactivity, and images (e.g., trainer photos, icons).

  - `css/styles.css` — Stylesheet for consistent styling across pages.  
  - `js/scripts.js` — JavaScript for UI behaviors like button clicks, filtering, and navigation.  
  - `images/` — Folder for storing images used in the app.

- **data/**  
  Stores all application data in text files as specified, used for reading and writing membership plans, classes, trainers, bookings, and workouts.

  - `memberships.txt` — Membership plans data.  
  - `classes.txt` — Fitness classes data.  
  - `trainers.txt` — Trainer profiles data.  
  - `bookings.txt` — Personal training session bookings data.  
  - `workouts.txt` — User workout records data.

This structure supports a clean separation of concerns, with a single backend file for simplicity, dedicated templates for each page, static assets for styling and interactivity, and a data folder for persistent storage in text files as required.
