My highest priority comment concerns Regulation #2 and #3 regarding the routing and URL structure:

**Comment:**
The code must ensure that the root URL `'/'` route exists and serves the Dashboard page as the first page, and all frontend navigation buttons and links must use Flask routing URLs (e.g., `url_for('dashboard')`) rather than local HTML file names or hardcoded paths. This is critical to make the website directly operable at `http://localhost:5000` and to maintain consistent navigation.

